ozone. 

Finally, a federally approvable enhanced I/M program represents one of the most cost-effective air quality control
strategies available. Without an effective I/M program, attainment of the ozone air quality standard is virtually
impossible, and without appropriate enabling legislation, an enhanced I/M program cannot be implemented. 



